cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the next generation network (NGN) environment and the need for bandwidth minimization, which is related to networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper focuses on providing multimedia services over high-speed networks and DVD quality video on demand, which falls under the category of multimedia. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The complete partitioning of the video on demand server is discussed in the paper, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the performance of the video on demand server, which can be related to social and information networks. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents analytical and simulation-based approaches to study the blockage probability of the server, which can be related to data structures and algorithms.
